com.slickqa.webdriver

Interface InFlow<T>


  • public interface InFlow<T>
    The InFlow interface enforces 3 methods: 1- if the browser's current page is itself 2- how to handle any forms on the page 3- how to continue past the page. To help provide information to accomplish this when you implement this interface you will need to define the type of context object that is used to handle and complete the page.
    Author:
    slambson

    • Method Detail

      • isCurrentPage

        boolean isCurrentPage()
        Determine if the browser's current page is the one represented by this class. It is VERY important that this be a quick check, not one that waits for 30 seconds before returning false. You should pass in a 0 timeout to whatever elements you look for in the browser.
        Returns:
        true if the current page is the one this class represents, false otherwise.
